<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD68E0DFF2DF933FC2EFAAC" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="587" pageId="1" pageNumber="586" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD68E0EFF2DF933FC8CF82E" blockId="1.[151,1437,1756,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD68E0EFF2DF933FE81F92A" bold="true" box="[151,365,1756,1783]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD68E0EFEC6F933FE0CF92A" box="[380,480,1756,1783]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1260,1284]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,386,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-115@2.[157,1431,381,1237]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus photographs Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. A. Male. B. Female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417195/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">Figs. 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD68E0EFE56F932FDBEF92A" box="[492,594,1757,1783]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1831,1855]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,181,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[153,1433,181,1807]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. A. Lateral view of male. B. Lateral view of female. C. Male tegmen. D. Female tegmen. E. Face in anterior view. F. Female ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417204/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">3A, C, E</figureCitation>
). Body size small for the genus. Head small, slightly wider than pronotum. Antennal scape as wide as rostrum. Eyes very large, laterally protruding, and slightly elongated in dorsal view. Cheek swelled. Clypeus slightly convex, anterior and posterior margin almost straight. Labrum relatively narrower than clypeus. Maxillary palpi somewhat extended, the third joint longer than the end one, and the end joint apically broad. Labial palpi relatively short, the end joint longer than the proximal two combined. Pronotum almost oblong and laterally hirsute. Tegmen extending to abdominal apex. Dorsal field bears five elevated longitudinal veins and false veins. Transverse veins between longitudinal veins inconspicuous. Hindwings absent. Tympanum absent. Hind legs long and hind tibiae armed with three pairs of dorsal spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD58E0DFF7DFF79FD8AFF24" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFF7DFF79FED9FF6D" bold="true" box="[199,309,150,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD58E0DFEFFFF78FE2DFF6C" box="[325,449,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[166,1391,739,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-222@4.[160,1427,739,1934]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia. A–C. Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. D–F. Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A, D. Dorsal view. B, E. Lateral view. C, F. Ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417207/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Fig. 4A–C</figureCitation>
). In dorsal view, epiphallus broad and apical margin of the epiphallic lateral lobe round. Ectoparamere bifurcated: the upper branch long, thin, apically blunt and slightly bent inwards; the lower branch conspicuously short and boomerang-like.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD58E0DFF7DFEECFB2EFEC0" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,357]" box="[199,1218,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFF7DFEECFEF2FEC0" bold="true" box="[199,286,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD58E0DFE94FEECFE7CFEC0" box="[302,400,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1260,1284]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,386,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-115@2.[157,1431,381,1237]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus photographs Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. A. Male. B. Female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417195/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Figs. 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD58E0DFE21FEECFE13FEC0" box="[411,511,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1831,1855]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,181,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[153,1433,181,1807]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. A. Lateral view of male. B. Lateral view of female. C. Male tegmen. D. Female tegmen. E. Face in anterior view. F. Female ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417204/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">3B, D, F</figureCitation>
). Body size slightly larger than male. Ovipositor blade-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD58E0DFF7DFEC9FCE2FEB8" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFF7DFEC9FEA3FE9D" bold="true" box="[199,335,294,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body blackish-brown. Eyes reddish. Tibiae, tarsus, tegmen, and cercus light yellowish. Except two dark brown proximal segments, antenna light yellowish.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF733CFCFFD58E0DFF2DFB03FB0DFAD9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417195" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6417195" box="[151,1249,1260,1285]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417195/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" startId="2.[151,250,1260,1284]" targetBox="[162,1425,386,1237]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD58E0DFF2DFB03FB0DFAD9" blockId="2.[151,1249,1260,1285]" box="[151,1249,1260,1285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFF2DFB03FEFFFAD9" bold="true" box="[151,275,1260,1284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Habitus photographs 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD58E0DFE48FB03FCE8FAD9" authority="He &amp; Wu &amp; Ma, 2022" authorityName="He &amp; Wu &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2022" box="[498,772,1260,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrumoculus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFE48FB03FCE8FAD9" box="[498,772,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Trigonidium rubrumoculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFCB0FB02FCB7FAD8" bold="true" box="[778,859,1261,1285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24B0D1DFFD58E0DFCB0FB02FCB7FAD8" box="[778,859,1261,1285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A. Male. B. Female. Scale bar: 2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD58E0DFF7DFADCFC2EFAAC" blockId="2.[151,1437,1330,1718]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFF7DFADCFE2EFA90" bold="true" box="[199,450,1331,1357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Measurements. Male</emphasis>
(n=2). BL 4.36±0.23, PL 0.87±0.08, TL 2.91±0.10, HFL 3.42±0.21; 
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFB74FADCFAC9FA90" bold="true" box="[1230,1317,1331,1357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Female</emphasis>
(n=2). BL 5.04±0.37, PL 1.02±0.13, TL 3.07±0.36, HFL 3.86±0.33, OL 1.72±0.41.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD58E0DFF7DFA94FCBBFA48" box="[199,855,1403,1429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD58E0DFF7DFA94FCBBFA48" blockId="2.[151,1437,1330,1718]" box="[199,855,1403,1429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFF7DFA94FEA2FA48" bold="true" box="[199,334,1403,1429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to the red eye of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD58E0DFF7DFA71FD90FA64" box="[199,636,1438,1465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD58E0DFF7DFA71FD90FA64" blockId="2.[151,1437,1330,1718]" box="[199,636,1438,1465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFF7DFA71FEB5FA65" bold="true" box="[199,345,1438,1464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD58E0DFED3FA70FE46FA64" box="[361,426,1439,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1686,1710]" captionTargetBox="[163,1426,666,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-84@1.[158,1430,662,1660]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Known distribution of Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. and Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. in China." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417191/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry id="F31B2CE4FFD58E0DFE78FA70FDE9FA64" box="[450,517,1439,1465]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49C8A296FFD58E0DFDAEFA70FD9CFA64" box="[532,624,1439,1465]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD58E0DFF7DFA2CFC30F96B" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD58E0DFF7DFA2CFC30F96B" blockId="2.[151,1437,1330,1718]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFF7DFA2CFEDCFA00" bold="true" box="[199,304,1475,1501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Remark.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD58E0DFD2CFA2CFBF2FA00" authority="Tan et al., 2019" authorityName="Tan" authorityYear="2019" box="[662,1054,1475,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solis">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFD2CFA2CFCB2FA00" box="[662,862,1475,1501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Trigonidium solis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D1185FFD58E0DFCDDFA2CFBF2FA00" author="Tan, M. K. &amp; Baroga-Barbecho, J. B. &amp; Yap, S. A." box="[871,1054,1475,1501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" pagination="573 - 587" refId="ref2800" refString="Tan, M. K., Baroga-Barbecho, J. B. &amp; Yap, S. A. (2019) Taxonomic notes on Trigonidium and related groups with one new species from the Philippines (Orthoptera: Trigonidiidae; Trigonidiinae). Zootaxa, 4564 (2), 573 - 587. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4564.2.13" type="journal article" year="2019">
Tan 
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFC21FA2CFC3AFA00" box="[923,982,1475,1501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<quantity id="4CF4C191FFD58E0DFC5CFA2CFBF2FA00" box="[998,1054,1475,1501]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.12826" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" unit="in" value="2019.0">2019</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in shape of ectoparamere (upper branch of ectoparamere is long and thin), but differs in its distinct coloration: blackish-brown body with yellowish tibiae and reddish eyes (body of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD58E0DFDB2F9E4FDBBF9F8" box="[520,599,1547,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solis">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFDB2F9E4FDBBF9F8" box="[520,599,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">T. solis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is yellowish). It differs from other members with similar coloration of the genus (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD58E0DFEA4F9C0FE21F994" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1838" box="[286,461,1583,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cicindeloides">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFEA4F9C0FE21F994" box="[286,461,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">T. cicindeloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD58E0DFE60F9C0FC00F994" authority="(Walker, 1869)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[474,1004,1582,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrocephamlum">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFE60F9C0FCD1F994" box="[474,829,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Trigonidium erythrocephamlum</emphasis>
(Walker, 1869)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD58E0DFB9BF9C0FF3CF9B0" authority="Ichikawa, 2001" authorityName="Ichikawa" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicum">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFB9BF9C0FAC4F995" box="[1057,1320,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Trigonidium japonicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D1185FFD58E0DFA95F9C0FF3CF9B0" author="Ichikawa, A." pageId="2" pageNumber="587" pagination="45 - 58" refId="ref2710" refString="Ichikawa, A. (2001) New species of Japanese crickets (Orthoptera; Grylloidea) with notes on certain taxa. Tettigonia: Memoirs of the Orthopterological Society of Japan, 3, 45 - 58" type="journal article" year="2001">Ichikawa, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) in bifurcated ectoparamere (inner edge of upper branch smooth and apically obtuse, and lower branch short and shaped as a boomerang). It differs 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD58E0DFDF6F998FBA5F94C" authority="Gorochov, 1987" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1987" box="[588,1097,1655,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubellongigrum">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD58E0DFDF6F998FC62F94C" box="[588,910,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Trigonidium rubellongigrum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D1185FFD58E0DFC2FF998FBA5F94C" author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[917,1097,1655,1681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" pagination="5 - 17" refId="ref2454" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1987) On the fauna of Orthoptera subfamilies Euscyrtinae, Trigonidiinae and Oecanthinae (Orthopera, Gryllidae) from eastern Indochina. In: Medvedev, L. N. (Ed.), Entomofauna V'etnama [Entomofauna of Vietnam]. Nauka, Moscow, pp. 5 - 17." type="book chapter" year="1987">Gorochov, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(female 
<typeStatus id="54B7D2D6FFD58E0DFB17F998FB33F94C" box="[1197,1247,1655,1681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">type</typeStatus>
) in color of eyes (red vs. black), pronotum (black vs. yellow), and femur (black vs. yellow).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
